Subject: CCSCNE conference

        The thirteenth annual conference of the Consortium for
Computing Sciences in Colleges, Northeast Division, will be held
at Wagner College, Staten Island, NY, on April 11-12, 2008, in
cooperation with ACM SIGCSE.
        We are pleased to announce that our two plenary-session
speakers will be Brian Kernighan (Princeton University and Bell Labs)
and Mary Beth Rosson (Penn State University).
        CCSCNE invites papers and proposals for panels, tutorials
or workshops on all aspects of undergraduate computing education.
Conference papers and abstracts of tutorials and panels will be
published in the Journal of Computing Sciences in Colleges, which
is part of the ACM Digital Library.
         Contributions on innovative courses and curricula in
two-year and four-year college programs; on the results of educational
research projects, classroom experiences or teaching techniques;
on societal or gender and diversity issues, distance education and
non-traditional students; on the use of new instructional technologies
or other aspects of pedagogy are all welcome.  We urge prospective
authors to look at the Journal of Computing Sciences in Colleges
to see what has been presented recently at CCSC conferences.
        The conference will also have a student poster session and a
programming contest.
        Please see http://www.ccscne.org/2008 for further details.

