Subject: Tenure-track Position at Macalester College

MACALESTER COLLEGE
Tenure-Track Computer Science Position

Macalester College invites applications for a tenure-track position in
Computer Science to begin fall 2008.  Rank is open. Candidates must have
completed a Ph.D. in Computer Science or a related field by the time of
appointment.  Preference will be given to applicants who can demonstrate
a commitment to excellence in teaching across the computer science
curriculum at the undergraduate level, who can develop a vigorous
research program that involves undergraduates, and who can contribute to
the broader intellectual life of the College. We seek a candidate with
expertise in an area of computer science that complements current
faculty interests.  This includes, but is not limited to, computer
security, distributed systems, embedded systems, networks, ubiquitous
computing, operating systems, or computer graphics.

Macalester College is a highly selective, private liberal arts college,
with a diverse student body of over 1800 undergraduates from 50 states
and over 90 countries.  The Department of Mathematics and Computer
Science is the largest department at the college, both in terms of
faculty and student enrollments. It offers majors in mathematics and
computer science.  The Department of Mathematics and Computer Science
values working closely with students on independent and research
projects, has a history of national leadership in curriculum
development, and encourages innovation in teaching at all levels.
Applicants should visit http://www.macalester.edu/mathcs for more
information about the college, department, and position.

Applicants may apply online via www.academicjobsonline.org, or may mail
application materials to Professor Susan Fox, Math/CS Dept., Macalester
College, 1600 Grand Avenue, St. Paul, MN 55105. Application materials
should include a resume, a statement of research interests, and a
statement of teaching interests and philosophy.  Applicants should
arrange for three letters of reference to be submitted, online or
through the mail.  Evaluation of applications will begin January 1, 2008
and continue until the position is filled.

As an Equal Opportunity employer supportive of affirmative efforts to
achieve diversity among its faculty, Macalester College strongly
encourage applications from women and members of underrepresented
minority groups.

